collection.description: This dataset contains temperature, salinity and pressure data for all profiles of the Argo float 2901092 managed by the Indian National Centre for Ocean Information Services (INCOIS).Argo is a major international collaborative project to observe the world's oceans and help scientists understand ocean processes and the ocean's roles in climate. The data collected also improves our ability to forecast climate and ocean conditions. The float drift at depth of between 1 and 2 km. Every ten days each float ascends to the surface, measuring temperature and salinity as it rises. This data is transmitted to satellites along with the float's position. The float then dives and starts a new cycle. The Argo float, WMO 2901092 was first deployed on the 2008-08-24T18:00:00 at launch location (Latitude : -1.0 ; Longitude : 81.53). The variables available for this Argo float are : Temperature, Practical Salinity and Pressure. The last location of the Argo float was transmitted on the 2013-12-08T14:23:56 at the following location (Latitude : -5.073 ; Longitude : 102.708).

collection.description: <p> A Visual Representation of Music & Aural Representation of Image:</p> <p> The <em>Intermedia Frottage </em>collection documents the development of compositional method for using graphic synthesis techniques to create sounds from images, and images from sounds. The products of these processes are then layered and arranged in cohesive, meaningful combinations. Moving back-and-forth between the two mediums in this dynamic interaction, a narrative interplay develops, connecting the materials created. Together with the sound compositions, the canvases and artists’ scorebooks tell this story. </p> <p> The collection consists of:</p> <ol> <li> 200pp. exegesis, text with 48 coloured figures,</li> <li> 14-track CD sound recording,</li> <li> Exhibition collection of 6 artists books and 10 giclee (digital print) canvases,</li> <li> DVD of images exhibition canvases and artists books,</li> <li> Exhibition copies of 14-track audio CD.</li> </ol> <p> The collection represents the complete body of work submitted by Melissa Cary to complete her PhD. The collection was exhibited at the Southern Cross University, NEXT Gallery as an installation of visual artworks accompanied by headphone listening stations with copies of the audio CD.</p>

collection.description: This dataset contains water level well data for the Thunderdome (GW075072) well site. This site is located within the Glenmore Park cluster of well sites. The dataset geospatial location is: Latitude: -33.793570459 Longitude: 150.6849502, with an elevation of 57m (AHD). The well has a drilled depth of 6.5 metres below ground level. Data was collected using Solinst Junior levellogger data loggers and YSI 6600 data sonde. High Performance Liquid Chromatography (HPLC), Inductively Coupled Plasma Atomic Emission Spectroscopy (ICP-AES), and Picarro Cavity Ring-Down Spectroscopy (CRDS) was used for chemical and isotope analysis. This data was collected between July 2011 and July 2013 to study and develop a conceptual model of shallow groundwater in Western Sydney which explains the observed geochemistry, the source of the groundwater, and the recharge and discharge of the groundwater. This dataset and associated research was funded by the New South Wales Department of Primary Industry.
Make research data accessible to individuals upon specific agreement with the researcher supplying the data

service.description: The Onshore Seismic Data of Australia is a collection of all land seismic traverses cross the Australian continent and its margins. The data includes raw and processed data in SEGY format. The metadata includes acquisition reports, processing reports, processed images, logs, and so on. The data acquisition was carried out in Australia from 1949-2012 by Geoscience Australia and various partners. The set of reflection and refraction data comprises over 12,000 km of coverage, and provides an insight into the variations in crustal architecture in the varied geological domains. The complete processed dataset was first available for public access in Oct 2013 (http://www.ga.gov.au/minerals/projects/current-projects/seismic-acquisition-processing.html ). The location of seismic traverses is shown by the Gallery link on the webpage. The new survey data will be updated on the webpage by the official data release date. The attribute structure of the dataset has also been revised to be more compatible with the GeoSciML data standard, published by the IUGS Commission for Geoscience Information. The onshore seismic data were collected with partner organizations: Australian Geodynamics Cooperative Research Centre, National Research Facility for Earth Sounding, Australian Nuclear Science and Technology Organisation, Cooperative Research Centre for Greenhouse Gas Technologies, Curtin University of Technology, Geological Survey of New South Wales, NSW Department of Mineral Resources, NSW Department of Primary Industries Mineral Resources, An organisation for a National Earth Science Infrastructure Program, Geological Survey Western Australia, Northern Territory Geological Survey, Primary Industries and Resources South Australia, Predictive Mineral Discovery Cooperative Research Centre, Queensland Geological Survey, GeoScience Victoria Department of Primary Industries, Tasmania Development and Resources, University of Western Australia.

collection.description: This dataset contains temperature, salinity and pressure data for all profiles of the Argo float 2901092 managed by the Indian National Centre for Ocean Information Services (INCOIS).Argo is a major international collaborative project to observe the world's oceans and help scientists understand ocean processes and the ocean's roles in climate. The data collected also improves our ability to forecast climate and ocean conditions. The float drift at depth of between 1 and 2 km. Every ten days each float ascends to the surface, measuring temperature and salinity as it rises. This data is transmitted to satellites along with the float's position. The float then dives and starts a new cycle. The Argo float, WMO 2901092 was first deployed on the 2008-08-24T18:00:00 at launch location (Latitude : -1.0 ; Longitude : 81.53). The variables available for this Argo float are : Temperature, Practical Salinity and Pressure. The last location of the Argo float was transmitted on the 2013-12-08T14:23:56 at the following location (Latitude : -5.073 ; Longitude : 102.708).

collection.description: <p>This dataset contains water level well data for the Glenmore Park, New South Wales, Australia. Data is collected from the following sites - Englewood (GW075071) - Thunderdome (GW075072) - Lakeside (GW075073) - Glengarry (GW075074) - Blue Hills Oval (GW075075) - Wetlands 2 (GW075084) - Wetlands 3 (GW075085) - Nada (GW075087) Data was collected using Solinst Junior levellogger data loggers and YSI 6600 data sonde. High Performance Liquid Chromatography (HPLC), Inductively Coupled Plasma Atomic Emission Spectroscopy (ICP-AES), and Picarro Cavity Ring-Down Spectroscopy (CRDS) was used for chemical and isotope analysis. This data was collected between July 2011 and July 2013 to study and develop a conceptual model of shallow groundwater in Western Sydney which explains the observed geochemistry, the source of the groundwater, and the recharge and discharge of the groundwater. This dataset and associated research was funded by the New South Wales Department of Primary Industry</p>
<p>Make research data accessible to individuals upon specific agreement with the researcher supplying the data</p>
